race.comment: Currie-trained EAST WEST MISS (5) switched from a Victorian stable and just missed at Rockhampton a month ago, first up. Four winners have come out of that, and with average luck from the outside gate, she can break through. SNUGG (7) rates well enough on her narrow defeat at Dalby on debut. She began awkwardly there following and was well beaten. The longer sprint should suit and a senior jockey takes over. She's been freshened and can get back on track. YONAKA (2) was on speed beaten a whisker here last time. Yet to miss the top-three in two runs at this circuit, and he may have turned the corner. WANNA KISS (8) debuts, and her trials suggest she'll be very competitive. The in-form Tilley sticks from those, and the betting will be key.
